caption: I love this place it has been Soooooo good over the last few months with closing at 1:15.It was so good I decided to go all out get a bigger pizza Italian beef fries wings kids meals,etc,picked up my order got home everything cold,even waited a extra 10-12 min after pick up time.They closed soon after now im putting everything in the oven🤦$70 worth😣every cook should be trained the same no matter the time..

We read the reviews and heard from 2 people that this restaurant was really good!  I wish I could agree, but unfortunately our visit was quite the opposite.  The water glasses were dirty, there was lipstick marks on a wine glass (not from the person drinking from it) & clumps of sediment in the bottom of the wine glass. Some of the salad was looking brown and ready for the waste can. Some of my ravioli was lukewarm when served, my husband ordered spaghetti with meat sauce, and there was no meat to be found. The sauce itself was really not tasting so good either. The entire dining room was dark & dingy, maybe for a reason? We muddled through dinner because we did not want to cause a problem, but we will never eat there again, or recommend it to anyone.

Had always wondered about this place. Always heard good things. I smelled coffee when I walked in so that prompted me to order one. Even something as simple as the coffee was great. I had the minestrone soup,  lasagna, and garlic bread. Everything was very simple but very tasty. The garlic bread had a twinge to it that I couldnt put my finger on, but it was still pretty good. Will have to come back here for sure.

The chicken parmesan with the salad, garlic bread and baked potato was excellent. My wife had the minestrone soup. It all tasted so fresh and authentic Italian. Our waitress was very friendly and attentive.

Delicious
It doesn't get any better than this for Italian food.

This is the family owned local Italian restaurant that you either grew up with or wish that you had.  Classic Italian-American red sauce dishes with house made sausage and meatballs.  I love the Italian beef here.  House dressing is red vinegar, small amount of olive oil, fresh garlic, dried herbs and a touch of sugar (hey, I don't know the recipe but can make an educated guess).  Recommended but you better like garlic!  I happen to love it.  Welcome to comfort food.  This is a restaurant that knows what it does well and doesn't try to be something its not.   Food snobs looking for edgy, trendy food won't find it here.  But, smart food snobs who get the big picture of dining out will get this place and be glad they gave it a try.
Wow, amazing people, amazing food. Excellent place with genuine Italian food. Great for a date, group of friends, or co-workers!

Wow. Started off with the calamari appetizers and finished every tentacle. Having to choose between the homemade minestrone soup and the salad with house vinnagrette was difficult, so I ordered both. A+++ With crispy lettuce, tomatoes, and onions I left an empty salad plate and soup bowl. For our entre, we had the ravioli and tortallini. Both great with perfect portion sizes and left me needing a mid-day nap when I was finished. The staff was so warm and inviting, I actually left the restaurant with a more positive outlook on life. In the words of Arnold... I'll be back. The only bad thing I have to say about this place is that I have to drive 11.5 hours from Augusta, GA to eat here. We finished our meal and just when I thought I was satisfied, the bill came. I was blown away that I received such exceptional food for such an amazing price. I will recommend this place to everyone that plans to visit Champaign. Awesome .

I am only giving this establishment one star because the salad and wine were good.  I ordered a dish that was supposed to have rigatoni,rustic cut tomatoes and sausage chunks with basil. It tasted like the cheapest generic pasta with a can of non salted generic stewed tomatoes poured over.  It was cold and what sausage was in there looked like someone took their cheap breakfast patty cut it into tiny squares and sprinkled it in. It was priced at $16.00.  I never saw the waitress again after she delivered food.  We were with a large group.  Others chose better than I but most weren't thrilled. The waitress argued with me saying it was their lightest dish and I told her it didn't say it was tasteless. She said she's see if they'd knock$ off the bill and I told her I was not payiong for it because it was inedible and I would have ordered something else if she would have come back before all were finished. Terrible food.  I will NEVER go back!
